    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-25T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="578"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1/1–2551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BDKE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d578fn1">Repeated to Frankfurt and London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-25T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 25, 1951—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4371. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 3834, January 19 (sent London
                    3966, repeated Frankfort 5027)<note n="2" xml:id="d578fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    and <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 4338, January 24 (repeated London
                    1051, Frankfort 501).<note n="3" xml:id="d578fn3">Not printed; it reported a
                        preliminary discussion with <persName corresp="#p_LRDLTG1">De la
                            Tournelle</persName> on the question of consultations with the Germans
                        (396.1/1–2451).</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> in accord on desirability consultation
                    with <gloss target="#t_FedRep1">FedRep</gloss> authorities when and if agreement
                    obtained on exploratory quadripartite talks re <gloss target="#t_CFM1"
                        >CFM</gloss>. Envisage such consultation on continuing basis “from time to
                    time,” i.e., without obligation on our part or formalization of procedures,
                    involving merely exchanges of views and information. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> agrees that this best done by <gloss target="#t_HICOM1"
                        >HICOM</gloss>s and that <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> is
                    logical opposite number, particularly as long as Germany has no Foreign
                    Minister. Re necessity eliciting views also of elements other than government
                    proper and coalition parties, <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> agrees
                    but understands this would not be done by <gloss target="#t_HICOM1"
                        >HICOM</gloss>s themselves but informally and perhaps on individual basis
                    rather than tripartitely, on somewhat lower level. Above is definitive <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> reply, cleared by <persName
                        corresp="#p_PA1">Parodi</persName> and consistent with what <persName
                        corresp="#p_LRDLTG1">La Tournelle</persName> told us yesterday. In
                    communicating views, <persName corresp="#p_SJ1">Sauvagnargues</persName> pointed
                    out however that practical problem will arise during first contacts with
                    Chancellor on subject <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss>, since <gloss
                        target="#t_HICOM1">HICOM</gloss>s will find it difficult to confine
                    themselves to eliciting German views, without themselves entering upon
                    discussion of such views. French want “discussion” with <persName
                        corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> in initial stage to be limited,
                    although they realize this will be difficult.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
